# 🎨 Design Token System & CSS Standards

## 🎯 **Design Token Categories**

### **Colors:**
```css
--primary-color: #4A90E2;
--primary-hover: #357ABD;
--success-color: #27AE60;
--error-color: #E74C3C;
--text-primary: #2C3E50;
--text-secondary: #7F8C8D;
--background-primary: #FFFFFF;
--background-secondary: #F8F9FA;
```

### **Spacing:**
```css
--space-xs: 0.25rem;  /* 4px */
--space-sm: 0.5rem;   /* 8px */
--space-md: 1rem;     /* 16px */
--space-lg: 1.5rem;   /* 24px */
--space-xl: 2rem;     /* 32px */
```

### **Typography:**
```css
--font-size-sm: 0.875rem;
--font-size-base: 1rem;
--font-size-lg: 1.125rem;
--font-weight-normal: 400;
--font-weight-medium: 500;
--font-weight-bold: 700;
```

## 🔧 **Component Base Classes**

### **Buttons:**
```css
.btn-base {
  padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
  transition: var(--transition-base);
}
```

### **Inputs:**
```css
.input-base {
  padding: var(--space-sm);
  border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  font-size: var(--font-size-base);
}
```

## 🚨 **CSS Standards**

### **DO:**
- ✅ Use design tokens for ALL spacing, colors, and typography
- ✅ Follow component base class patterns
- ✅ Use semantic CSS custom properties
- ✅ Maintain mobile-first responsive design
- ✅ Use logical properties (margin-inline-start vs margin-left)

### **DON'T:**
- ❌ Hard-code colors, spacing, or font sizes
- ❌ Use inline styles in HTML
- ❌ Break the established component patterns
- ❌ Add styles without considering mobile impact

